'''Oliver Reck''' (born [[February 27]], [[1965]] in [[Frankfurt am Main]]) is a [[German people|German]] football goalkeeper, who played mostly for [[Kickers Offenbach]], [[Werder Bremen]] and [[Schalke 04]].

He played for [[Germany national football team]] and won bronze medal at the [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Olympic Games]] and won the [[1996 UEFA European Football Championship|Euro 1996]]. He earned only one cap, a 9-1 win against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] just before Euro 1996.

Although [[Oliver Kahn]] holds the record for most matches without conceding goals in the [[Fu<U+00DF>ball-Bundesliga|Bundesliga]], at 180 in a total of 515 matches, Oliver Reck is the most effective goalkeeper, not conceding a goal in 173 of 471 matches. His "effectivity rate" is 0.367, versus 0.349 of Oliver Kahn.

